title: Does she care about your low follower count? Shocking reveal…

channel_info.title: Robbie Kramer
channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "What if he doesn't have an Instagram or he has three photos and he's got like 200 followers? We love that. We love a guy that's barely on social media because that means he actually is a person who doesn't really care about certain stuff like that. There was an example, like I went to brunch with my sister and my brother-in-law and my best friend. We were all just laughing and then the waiter comes over and like, oh yeah, that guy over there wants to buy you a drink. And I looked at him and I was like, which guy? And he like shows me him and I'm like... Is the guy looking at the same time? He was staring and I felt so uncomfortable. And like I whispered to my girlfriend, I'm like, do I take it? She's like, just take it. Be nice. And I'm like, but I don't want him to think like he has a chance if I take it. Not to be rude. Also, it's the brunch. Like I'm not drinking. I'm also hungover from the night before. Like the last thing I want to do is drink more. Yeah, if you take the drink, he's coming over. Well, that's the thing. So my girlfriend, she's like, no, just take it. I'm like, OK. She's like, OK, well, what do you want? And I just like order a Mexican meal and I'm just kind of like, OK. And then you know when you feel someone's eyes on you? And I felt like I had to say thank you. So I just looked at him and he looked at me and he was like, he winked at me. And I was just kind of like, right, what do I do now? Right. Yeah. And I was.
